26  * .configure. mbmaxlen_big5=2

35 /*
36  Support for Chinese(BIG5) characters, by jou@nematic.ieo.nctu.edu.tw
37  modified by Wei He (hewei@mail.ied.ac.cn)
38  modified by Alex Barkov <bar@udm.net>
39 */
40 
41 #define isbig5head(c) (0xa1<=(uchar)(c) && (uchar)(c)<=0xf9)
42 #define isbig5tail(c) ((0x40<=(uchar)(c) && (uchar)(c)<=0x7e) || \
43  (0xa1<=(uchar)(c) && (uchar)(c)<=0xfe))
44 
45 #define isbig5code(c,d) (isbig5head(c) && isbig5tail(d))
46 #define big5code(c,d) (((uchar)(c) <<8) | (uchar)(d))
47 #define big5head(e) ((uchar)(e>>8))
48 #define big5tail(e) ((uchar)(e&0xff))

839 static int my_strnncoll_big5_internal(const uchar **a_res,
840  const uchar **b_res, size_t length)
841 {
842  const uchar *a= *a_res, *b= *b_res;
843 
844  while (length--)
845  {
846  if ((length > 0) && isbig5code(*a,*(a+1)) && isbig5code(*b, *(b+1)))
847  {
848  if (*a != *b || *(a+1) != *(b+1))
849  return ((int) big5code(*a,*(a+1)) -
850  (int) big5code(*b,*(b+1)));
851  a+= 2;
852  b+= 2;
853  length--;
854  }
855  else if (sort_order_big5[*a++] !=
856  sort_order_big5[*b++])
857  return ((int) sort_order_big5[a[-1]] -
858  (int) sort_order_big5[b[-1]]);
859  }
860  *a_res= a;
861  *b_res= b;
862  return 0;
863 }
864 
865 
866 /* Compare strings */
867 
868 static int my_strnncoll_big5(CHARSET_INFO *cs __attribute__((unused)),
869  const uchar *a, size_t a_length,
870  const uchar *b, size_t b_length,
871  my_bool b_is_prefix)
872 {
873  size_t length= min(a_length, b_length);
874  int res= my_strnncoll_big5_internal(&a, &b, length);
875  return res ? res : (int)((b_is_prefix ? length : a_length) - b_length);
876 }
877 
878 
879 /* compare strings, ignore end space */
880 
881 static int my_strnncollsp_big5(CHARSET_INFO * cs __attribute__((unused)),
882  const uchar *a, size_t a_length,
883  const uchar *b, size_t b_length,
884  my_bool diff_if_only_endspace_difference)
885 {
886  size_t length= min(a_length, b_length);
887  int res= my_strnncoll_big5_internal(&a, &b, length);
888 
889 #ifndef VARCHAR_WITH_DIFF_ENDSPACE_ARE_DIFFERENT_FOR_UNIQUE
890  diff_if_only_endspace_difference= 0;
891 #endif
892 
893  if (!res && a_length != b_length)
894  {
895  const uchar *end;
896  int swap= 1;
897  if (diff_if_only_endspace_difference)
898  res= 1; /* Assume 'a' is bigger */
899  /*
900  Check the next not space character of the longer key. If it's < ' ',
901  then it's smaller than the other key.
902  */
903  if (a_length < b_length)
904  {
905  /* put longer key in a */
906  a_length= b_length;
907  a= b;
908  swap= -1; /* swap sign of result */
909  res= -res;
910  }
911  for (end= a + a_length-length; a < end ; a++)
912  {
913  if (*a != ' ')
914  return (*a < ' ') ? -swap : swap;
915  }
916  }
917  return res;
918 }

921 static size_t my_strnxfrm_big5(CHARSET_INFO *cs __attribute__((unused)),
922  uchar *dest, size_t len,
923  const uchar *src, size_t srclen)
924 {
925  uint16 e;
926  size_t dstlen= len;
927  uchar *dest_end= dest + dstlen;
928 
929  len = srclen;
930  while (len-- && dest < dest_end)
931  {
932  if ((len > 0) && isbig5code(*src, *(src+1)))
933  {
934  e = big5strokexfrm((uint16) big5code(*src, *(src+1)));
935  *dest++ = big5head(e);
936  if (dest < dest_end)
937  *dest++ = big5tail(e);
938  src +=2;
939  len--;
940  } else
941  *dest++ = sort_order_big5[(uchar) *src++];
942  }
943  if (dstlen > srclen)
944  bfill(dest, dstlen - srclen, ' ');
945  return dstlen;
946 }

6753 static int func_uni_big5_onechar(int code){
6754  if ((code>=0x00A2)&&(code<=0x00F7))
6755  return(tab_uni_big50[code-0x00A2]);
6756  if ((code>=0x02C7)&&(code<=0x0451))

6758  if ((code>=0x2013)&&(code<=0x22BF))
6759  return(tab_uni_big52[code-0x2013]);
6760  if ((code>=0x2460)&&(code<=0x2642))
6761  return(tab_uni_big53[code-0x2460]);
6762  if ((code>=0x3000)&&(code<=0x3129))
6763  return(tab_uni_big54[code-0x3000]);
6764  if ((code>=0x32A3)&&(code<=0x32A3))
6765  return(tab_uni_big55[code-0x32A3]);
6766  if ((code>=0x338E)&&(code<=0x33D5))
6767  return(tab_uni_big56[code-0x338E]);
6768  if ((code>=0x4E00)&&(code<=0x9483))
6769  return(tab_uni_big57[code-0x4E00]);
6770  if ((code>=0x9577)&&(code<=0x9FA4))
6771  return(tab_uni_big58[code-0x9577]);
6772  if ((code>=0xFA0C)&&(code<=0xFA0D))
6773  return(tab_uni_big59[code-0xFA0C]);
6774  if ((code>=0xFE30)&&(code<=0xFFFD))

6780 static int
6781 my_wc_mb_big5(CHARSET_INFO *cs __attribute__((unused)),
6782  my_wc_t wc, uchar *s, uchar *e)
6783 {
6784 
6785  int code;
6786 
6787  if (s >= e)
6788  return MY_CS_TOOSMALL;
6789 
6790  if ((int) wc < 0x80)
6791  {
6792  s[0]= (uchar) wc;
6793  return 1;
6794  }
6795 
6796  if (!(code=func_uni_big5_onechar(wc)))
6797  return MY_CS_ILUNI;
6798 
6799  if (s+2>e)
6800  return MY_CS_TOOSMALL;
6801 
6802  s[0]=code>>8;
6803  s[1]=code&0xFF;
6804 
6805  return 2;
6806 }

6809 static int
6810 my_mb_wc_big5(CHARSET_INFO *cs __attribute__((unused)),
6811  my_wc_t *pwc,const uchar *s,const uchar *e)
6812 {
6813 
6814  int hi;
6815 
6816  if (s >= e)
6817  return MY_CS_TOOSMALL;
6818 
6819  if ((hi= s[0]) < 0x80)
6820  {
6821  pwc[0]=hi;
6822  return 1;
6823  }
6824 
6825  if (s+2>e)
6826  return MY_CS_TOOSMALL2;
6827 
6828  if (!(pwc[0]=func_big5_uni_onechar((hi<<8)+s[1])))
6829  return -2;
6830 
6831  return 2;
6832 }

6835 /*
6836  Returns a well formed length of a BIG5 string.
6837  CP950 and HKSCS additional characters are also accepted.
6838 */
6839 static
6840 size_t my_well_formed_len_big5(CHARSET_INFO *cs __attribute__((unused)),
6841  const char *b, const char *e,
6842  size_t pos, int *error)
6843 {
6844  const char *b0= b;
6845  const char *emb= e - 1; /* Last possible end of an MB character */
6846 
6847  *error= 0;
6848  while (pos-- && b < e)
6849  {
6850  if ((uchar) b[0] < 128)
6851  {
6852  /* Single byte ascii character */
6853  b++;
6854  }
6855  else if ((b < emb) && isbig5code((uchar)*b, (uchar)b[1]))
6856  {
6857  /* Double byte character */
6858  b+= 2;
6859  }
6860  else
6861  {
6862  /* Wrong byte sequence */
6863  *error= 1;
6864  break;
6865  }
6866  }
6867  return (size_t) (b - b0);
6868 }
